oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector

Class RecordInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.spatial.hadoop.vector.RecordInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class RecordInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Writable class that contains a subset of the data of a certain record called source record, typically, the record's id and spatial information as a JGeometry instance. It may also contain information used to find the source record such as the path of the file where the record is stored, its start position and length in bytes. Additional information can be added as text fields which can be stored and retrieved. Note that as extra fields are added it will also increase the size of the RecordInfo instances when stored at disk.
    Author:
    hsaucedo
